narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it. It is not a lot of work, and you learn a lot.

Conducting will probably not be as challenging as other music classes, if you're a music major. The requirements are not intense, and it's a very low-key environment. If you're looking to learn more about conducting, but you're a little shy about actually getting up in front of an orchestra with a baton, this is a great place to start out.

It's a good class - you get a fair amount of podium time (depending on the class size, half of this semester's class was grad students who didn't even show up half the time). Rep for this semester was Beethoven 9 finale, Tchaik 5 II, and last part of the Rite of Spring.
